<https://www.gov.uk/government/people/keith-stewart> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "Keith Stewart KC was Advocate General for Scotland from October 2020 to July 2024. Education Keith attended Dirleton Primary School and George Heriot’s School, Edinburgh before going to Keble College, Oxford. Keith continued his education at the University of Edinburgh and the University of Strathclyde. Career Keith was called to the Bar in 1993 and took silk in 2011. He specialises in criminal law, and has advised in other matters including defamation and intellectual property. Personal Life Keith lives in North Berwick and is married with two children."@en .
